ygData.subject: Re: [EverQuest] List been quiet lately
ygData.msgSnippet: that is a loaded question...  personally, I prefer unrest, even with all the trains, due to the fact that there are more areas to set up groups, and is easier
ygData.messageBody:
that is a loaded question...  personally, I prefer unrest, even with all the trains, due to the fact that there are more areas to set up groups, and is easier to solo, also.  high pass and high keep are nice, but there are only a few places to set up groups in those areas, and so spots in groups are hard to come by during primetime.
 
Rich
----- Original Message -----
From: Rob LeBeau
To: EverQuest@yahoogroups.com
Sent: Thursday, June 27, 2002 9:48 AM
Subject: Re: [EverQuest] List been quiet lately

No way Baby.
EQ lives...................lol

Ok How about this topic.
What do you all prefer..............(loaded question )
Unrest or High Pass and High Keep.

I have played in both and like them a lot but I am not
sure which I prefer.  The issue I have with Unrest is
that the closest bind/sell point is Kaladim or
Kelethin for noncasters.

I have also seen that Unrest drops some of the best or
most sought after stuff in the game. Most stuff I have
been looting is ok but I would not say Fantastic.
NOW...I am only level 19 Ranger and pulling from the
1st floor.  Does Unrest get better as you go up in
level?

The thing I like about High Keep is that I can bank
there and bind there.

Your thoughts appreciated.

Thanks

Rob
